  <section class="intro">
    <h2>What is UPI & Online Banking?</h2>
    <p>
      UPI (Unified Payments Interface) allows instant money transfer between bank accounts using a mobile app. 
      Online banking enables access to accounts, transfers, and bill payments digitally. 
      While convenient, they require extra care to avoid fraud and scams.
    </p>
  </section>

  
  <section class="importance">
    <h2>Why Security is Important?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Protects your hard-earned money from fraudsters.</li>
      <li>Ensures safe online transactions without theft.</li>
      <li>Builds trust in digital payments.</li>
      <li>Prevents unauthorized access to your accounts.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  
  <section class="risks">
    <h2>Common UPI & Banking Frauds</h2>

    <div class="step">
      <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/3135/3135715.png" alt="Phishing Logo" width="80">
      <div>
        <h3>1. Phishing & Fake Calls</h3>
        <p>Fraudsters trick you with fake emails, SMS, or calls pretending to be from your bank or UPI app.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/1077/1077012.png" alt="Hacking Logo" width="80">
      <div>
        <h3>2. Hacking & Unauthorized Access</h3>
        <p>Hackers may try to access your banking apps or accounts to steal information.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/565/565547.png" alt="Fraud Logo" width="80">
      <div>
        <h3>3. UPI Fraud Requests</h3>
        <p>Scammers send fake UPI payment requests asking you to approve transactions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/483/483408.png" alt="OTP Logo" width="80">
      <div>
        <h3>4. OTP Sharing</h3>
        <p>Fraudsters ask you to share OTPs (One-Time Passwords) to steal money. Never share your OTP.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

 
  <section class="tips">
    <h2>Safety Tips for UPI & Banking</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Never share your PIN, password, or OTP with anyone.</li>
      <li>Use only official banking & UPI apps.</li>
      <li>Always verify payment requests before approving.</li>
      <li>Enable two-factor authentication for extra protection.</li>
      <li>Report suspicious messages or transactions immediately to your bank.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

 
